question.en:
Consider this code:
SELECT col1, col2, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY col1 ORDER BY col2 DESC) as rn FROM table1;
Which rows will be returned if you add a WHERE clause: WHERE rn <= 2?

